Coding plan:
"### File Structure
```
travelplanner/
│
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
├── README.md
│
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── destinations.html
│   ├── destination_details.html
│   ├── itinerary.html
│   ├── accommodations.html
│   ├── transportation.html
│   ├── packages.html
│   ├── trips.html
│   ├── booking_confirmation.html
│   └── recommendations.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (destination and package images)
│
└── data/
    ├── destinations.txt
    ├── itineraries.txt
    ├── hotels.txt
    ├── flights.txt
    ├── packages.txt
    ├── trips.txt
    └── bookings.txt
```

### File Descriptions
```
- app.py
  The main backend Python application file implementing the web server using a lightweight framework (e.g., Flask). It handles routing for all ten pages, processes user inputs, reads/writes data from/to the local text files in the 'data' directory, and renders HTML templates with dynamic content.

- requirements.txt
  Lists Python dependencies required to run the application (e.g., Flask, any PDF generation libraries).

- README.md
  Documentation file describing the project setup, running instructions, and overview.

- templates/
  Contains all HTML template files for the web application pages, each corresponding to one of the ten pages defined in the requirements. Templates use placeholders for dynamic data populated by app.py.

  - dashboard.html: Dashboard page layout with featured destinations and upcoming trips.
  - destinations.html: List and filter/search destinations.
  - destination_details.html: Detailed view of a selected destination.
  - itinerary.html: Itinerary planning and management interface.
  - accommodations.html: Hotel search and filter page.
  - transportation.html: Flight booking page.
  - packages.html: Travel packages listing and booking.
  - trips.html: Trip management page.
  - booking_confirmation.html: Booking confirmation details and options.
  - recommendations.html: Personalized travel recommendations and trending destinations.

- static/
  Contains static assets like CSS, JavaScript, and images.

  - css/styles.css: Stylesheet for consistent UI styling.
  - js/scripts.js: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filters).
  - images/: Folder for storing images used in destination cards, packages, etc.

- data/
  Stores all application data in text files as specified, used for reading and persisting information.

  - destinations.txt: Destination data.
  - itineraries.txt: Itinerary data.
  - hotels.txt: Hotel/accommodation data.
  - flights.txt: Flight data.
  - packages.txt: Travel package data.
  - trips.txt: User trips data.
  - bookings.txt: Booking records.
```
This structure keeps the backend logic centralized in one Python file for simplicity, while separating frontend templates and static assets for maintainability and clarity. The local text files in the data folder serve as the persistent storage as required."

